<h2>Core Definition</h2>
<p>“Core Definition” specifies how a Valiterm term is expressed as machine-readable data: identity, description, allowed placements, and multilingual reasoning aids.</p>

<h3>Essentials</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Stable <code>@id</code> (URI) and <code>name</code></li>
  <li><code>description</code> in English, with optional localized keys (e.g., <code>description-sv</code>)</li>
  <li><code>allowedIn</code> lists consuming entities (e.g., <code>DefinedTerm</code>, <code>Product</code>, <code>HowTo</code>)</li>
  <li>Reasoning hints (<code>reasoning</code>, <code>reasoning-sv</code>, …) to help AI interpret usage</li>
</ul>

<h3>Example (inline)</h3>
<pre>
&lt;section id="hasCoreUseCase" itemscope itemtype="https://valiterm.org/PropertyValue"&gt;
  &lt;meta itemprop="description" content="Describes the primary or intended use case for a product or material." /&gt;
  &lt;meta itemprop="valueType" content="text" /&gt;
  &lt;meta itemprop="allowedIn" content="DefinedTerm" /&gt;
  &lt;meta itemprop="allowedIn" content="Product" /&gt;
  &lt;meta itemprop="allowedIn" content="HowTo" /&gt;
  &lt;meta itemprop="reasoning" content="Helps AI understand domain-specific usage patterns for recommendation and classification." /&gt;
  &lt;meta itemprop="status" content="accepted" /&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;
</pre>

